com.samskivert.depot.util

Class Tuple2<A,B>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.samskivert.depot.util.Tuple2<A,B>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Tuple2<A,B>
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Contains a two column result. This class is immutable and the objects it references are also meant to be immutable. They will generally contain only Depot primitive types (Java primitives, SQL primitives and some array types), which should be treated as immutable.
    See Also:
